e. The hanging\n\u00b0re framed ,n mahogany with\ngold decorations. Eight pieces, in\ncluding Twin Beds. _\nRegular Price $320_ $22$\nAmerican Chippendale Bed Room\nGroup, following the Chippendale\nChinese motif. Genuine Honduras\nmahogany construction, finished in\nred-brown tone. Each piece is splen\ndidly proportioned and very decora\nBeds E'9ht P'eces' includin9 Twin\nRegular Price $350... $240\nAmerican Empire Bed Room Group\nsturdy in its effect and charming in\ntne proportions of each piece. Gen\nuine Cuban and Honduras mahogdny\nconstruction. Bed panels and drawer\nfronts are paneled in figured ma\nhogany. Eight pieces, including Twin\nBeds.\nRegular Price $595_\nAmerican Heppelwhite Bed Room\nGroup, with quaint sleigh-type bed.\nGenuine Honduras mahogany, in the\nlovely old red tone. Most effective\nhanging mirrors. Eight pieces in\ncluding Twin Beds.\nRegular Price $365_\nLouis XVI Bed Room Group in French\nwalnut, with old white and gold hang\ning mirrors. A seven-piece qroup\nwith full-size bed.\nRegular Price $600_\nAmerican Colonial Bed Room Group\nwith gracefully designed tall poster\nTwin Beds; Bureau, Chest-on-Chest\nand Dressing Table handsomely\ncarved. Hanging mirrors are gold\nfinished, topped with urn. Genuine\nHonduras mahogany construction.\nEight pieces including\nTwin Beds.\nRegular Price $385_\nDining Room Groups\nbheraton Dining Group, with serpen\ntine-front Sideboard and Server; prac\ntical China Case; double-pedestal\nDining Table; one Armchair and six\nSide Chairs, all handsomely carved.\nGenuine Honduras mahogany con\nstruction, with satinwood inlays. Com\nplete with ten pieces. 4\nRegular Price $1,070_\nAmerican Heppelwhite Dining Group;\ngenuine Honduras mahogany with\nhandsomely figured doors ond drawer\nfronts. You will note the graceful\nlines of each piece; how perfectly\nproportioned and rich the effect in the\nred finish. Complete with\nten pieces.\nRegular Price $390_\nEarly English Jacobean Dining Group,\nwith all the sturdiness and charm of\nthis famous school. Executed in Eng\nlish oak of selected grain and finished\nin the true Early English oak color\nsuch as is found in the old cathedrals.\nChairs are covered in antiqued leather.\nComplete in ten pieces.\nRegular Price S56S_\nAmerican Colonial Dining Group, fol\nlowing the Sheraton school, created\nin genuine Honduras mahogany. The\nSideboard is especially interesting with\nits simulated tambour front. China\nCabinet, Server, Double-pedestal Din\ning Table, one Master Chair and five\nSide Chairs complete this ten-piece\ngroup.\nRegular Price S355_ $XO\u00a9\nBritish Colonial Dining Group, a new\nthought in dining room furniture de\nsign, executed in genuine Honduras\nmahogany. Distinctive in type; sub\nstantial in construction; decorative in\neffect\u2014a design which will fit into\neither a modern scheme or a traditional\none. Complete with ten\npieces.\nRegular Price $495_ $25\u00a9\nSheraton Dining Group, genuine Hon\nduras mahogany inlaid with broad\nbands of satinwood. The doors and\ndrawer fronts are finished with beeu\ntifully figured crotch mahogany.\nComplete with ten pieces.\nRegular Price S350_\nW. J. Sloane 711 Twelfth St.\nCourtesy Parking, Capital Garage Convenient Charge Accounts\nI\u2014\u2014\u2014","height":"31112","width":"22528"}}
